---
layout: base.njk
permalink: /blog/
pageKey: blog
title: "Blog: Hiring EAs, Chiefs of Staff & Ops | Abraham Otieno"
description: "Long-form writing on hiring executive assistants, building chief-of-staff roles, operations systems, and remote work for founders."
keywords: "executive assistant blog, EA hiring guide, chief of staff vs EA, remote operations Africa, executive assistant Kenya guide"
ogTitle: "The Blog | Hiring & Operations for Founders"
ogDescription: "Hiring guides, role comparisons, real cost numbers, and operating frameworks."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Blog", url: "/blog/" }
---

<section class="section hero" style="padding-bottom: var(--space-7);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-inner reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Blog</span>
      <h1>Writing on <em>Hiring, Operations &amp; Executive Support</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Long-form pieces for founders, CEOs, and operations leaders. No fluff, no listicles, just the work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="post-list reveal">
      {% set posts = collections.post | reverse %}
      {% for post in posts %}
        <a class="post-card" href="{{ post.url }}">
          {% if post.data.eyebrow %}<span class="eyebrow">{{ post.data.eyebrow }}</span>{% endif %}
          <h3>{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
          <p>{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <time datetime="{{ post.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.date.toDateString() }}</time>
            {% if post.data.readTime %} · {{ post.data.readTime }} min read{% endif %}
          </div>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% include "partials/landing-cta.njk" %}
